subSubSection.paragraph:
Two shells from Station 95 are quite similar to the previous species [
Triphora patricia
], but less slender; the edge of the last whorl is less pronounced and even includes a second thread. There are about 9 whorls, which are initially shaped and sculptured as in the previous species, again having three rows of tubercles and a smooth thread. This forms on the last whorl an edge, which is somewhat obtuse, under this edge there are still two threads visible. Siphonal canal moderately long, straight; diamond-shaped aperture. Height 5 mm, diameter 1.6 mm.
